# LiftLog — Project Context

## What This Is
A personal workout tracking web app. React (Vite) frontend, Express/Node.js backend, PostgreSQL database, Drizzle ORM, Tailwind CSS.

## Specs Live in `docs/`
Before starting any feature, check the relevant spec doc:
- `docs/README.md` — index of all docs and current phase
- `docs/01-tech-stack.md` — stack decisions and repo structure
- `docs/02-database-schema.md` — tables and relationships
- `docs/03-api-design.md` — REST endpoints
- `docs/04-ui-home.md` through `docs/07-exercise-library.md` — UI specs

## Rules
- Stay within the defined stack. Do not introduce new libraries without asking.
- No auth yet — single-user, local-first for MVP.
- Mobile-first UI. Test layouts at 375px width.
- Keep backend routes in `backend/src/routes/`, controllers in `backend/src/controllers/`.